summary: Comprehensive comparison of all 8 Relume projects (MezTal 1-7 and MezTa 8), analyzing structure depth, Solutions/Industries coverage, total page counts, and alignment with project requirements. Identifies MezTa 8 as potentially superior to the currently selected MezTal 5 due to more comprehensive Solutions coverage (12 vs 9-10 pages), higher total page count (30-35 vs 25-30), and more detailed wireframe content. Includes detailed breakdowns of each project's hierarchy, a summary comparison matrix, critical findings about MezTa 8's advantages, and recommendations with pros/cons for either switching to MezTa 8 or continuing with MezTal 5. Requires user decision on which project to use as the base for expansion.
